coder v0.0.0-devel

USAGE:
  coder secret update [flags] <name>

  Update a secret

  At least one of --value, --value-env, --description, --env, or --file must be
  specified. Provide the secret value by at most one of --value, --value-env, or
  non-interactive stdin (pipe or redirect).

OPTIONS:
      --description string
          Update the secret description. Pass an empty string to clear it.

      --env string
          Update the environment variable injection target. Pass an empty string
          to clear it.

      --file string
          Update the file injection target. Pass an empty string to clear it.

      --trim-trailing-newline bool
          Trim a single trailing newline from stdin-provided secret values.

      --value string
          Update the secret value. For security reasons, prefer --value-env or
          non-interactive stdin (pipe or redirect).

      --value-env string
          Read the updated secret value from the named environment variable.

———
Run `coder --help` for a list of global options.
